The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | Police relief
                                                                                                                     4                                                                                      Police relief
                            
	Calcutta: The government today announced that the kin of police personnel killed on duty in Maoist-hit areas would get Rs 15 lakh and a job.         
	There will be a Rs 10-lakh insurance cover and an ex-gratia of Rs 5 lakh. Besides, a member of the dead jawans family will be get a job, the chief minister said at an awards programme for meritorious personnel.                                                                                                                                                            
